<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news">"<a href="http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=FB0911F8385A127A93C1A91788D85F4D8285F9" class="external text" title="http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=FB0911F8385A127A93C1A91788D85F4D8285F9" rel="nofollow">Roerich Nominated for Peace Award</a>". <i><a href="/wiki/New_York_Times" title="New York Times" class="mw-redirect">New York Times</a></i>. March 3, 1929<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=FB0911F8385A127A93C1A91788D85F4D8285F9" class="external free" title="http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=FB0911F8385A127A93C1A91788D85F4D8285F9" rel="nofollow">http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=FB0911F8385A127A93C1A91788D85F4D8285F9</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2009-02-03</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Roerich+Nominated+for+Peace+Award&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BNew+York+Times%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=March+3%2C+1929&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fselect.nytimes.com%2Fgst%2Fabstract.html%3Fres%3DFB0911F8385A127A93C1A91788D85F4D8285F9&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Nicholas_Roerich"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
